{"body": "I am not sure if there is a need for another file, `config/application.rb` can be a better option as you said. \n\nHowever, whether\n\n+ you use release dates as a version number \n+ you use \"x.y.z\" \n+ you give version names\n+ you don't version ur app\n\nI wish rails had a convention to do that.\n\nThis constant can be used by many things such as deployment scripts, ci systems, testing purposes, documentation purposes, logging, monitoring tools, etc.\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6802994", "created_at": "2012-07-06T11:45:05Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6983#issuecomment-6802994", "updated_at": "2012-07-06T11:45:05Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6983, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/oguzbilgic", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/523b735c515f4f89e7f4f1f31d2add74?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F85704a4d6a38e3883081a8a27c101e9c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/received_events", "gravatar_id": "523b735c515f4f89e7f4f1f31d2add74", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "oguzbilgic", "type": "User", "id": 144778, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/oguzbilgic/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380135bd3543c15100c0f0"}, "id": 6802994, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6983"}
